features.name: PEP_mutase Catalyzes the thermodynamically favored C-C bond cleavage of (2R,3S)-2-methylisocitrate to yield pyruvate and succinate

DAO,Methyltransf_30 Catalyzes the last two steps in the biosynthesis of 5- methylaminomethyl-2-thiouridine (mnm(5)s(2)U) at the wobble position (U34) in tRNA. Catalyzes the FAD-dependent demodification of cmnm(5)s(2)U34 to nm(5)s(2)U34, followed by the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to nm(5)s(2)U34, to form mnm(5)s(2)U34
Aminotran_3 intramolecular transferase activity, transferring amino groups
TerC Integral membrane protein TerC family

PolyA_pol,PolyA_pol_RNAbd,PolyA_pol_arg_C Adds poly(A) tail to the 3' end of many RNAs, which usually targets these RNAs for decay. Plays a significant role in the global control of gene expression, through influencing the rate of transcript degradation, and in the general RNA quality control
HPPK Protein involved in 2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-hydroxymethyldihydropteridine diphosphokinase activity and folic acid-containing compound biosynthetic process
Aconitase,Aconitase_C Catalyzes the isomerization of citrate to isocitrate via cis-aconitate

THF_DHG_CYH,THF_DHG_CYH_C Catalyzes the oxidation of 5,10- methylenetetrahydrofolate to 5,10-methenyltetrahydrofolate and then the hydrolysis of 5,10-methenyltetrahydrofolate to 10- formyltetrahydrofolate
RsmJ Specifically methylates the adenine in position 2030 of 23S rRNA
HAGH_C,Lactamase_B Thiolesterase that catalyzes the hydrolysis of S-D- lactoyl-glutathione to form glutathione and D-lactic acid
IspA probably involved in intracellular septation
Response_reg,Trans_reg_C Transcriptional regulatory protein, C terminal
HTH_Tnp_1 PFAM transposase IS3 IS911 family protein
Response_reg,Trans_reg_C Transcriptional regulatory protein, C terminal

HHH_5,RuvA_C,RuvA_N The RuvA-RuvB complex in the presence of ATP renatures cruciform structure in supercoiled DNA with palindromic sequence, indicating that it may promote strand exchange reactions in homologous recombination. RuvAB is a helicase that mediates the Holliday junction migration by localized denaturation and reannealing. RuvA stimulates, in the presence of DNA, the weak ATPase activity of RuvB

RuvC Nuclease that resolves Holliday junction intermediates in genetic recombination. Cleaves the cruciform structure in supercoiled DNA by nicking to strands with the same polarity at sites symmetrically opposed at the junction in the homologous arms and leaves a 5'-terminal phosphate and a 3'-terminal hydroxyl group

HgmA Involved in the catabolism of homogentisate (2,5- dihydroxyphenylacetate or 2,5-OH-PhAc), a central intermediate in the degradation of phenylalanine and tyrosine. Catalyzes the oxidative ring cleavage of the aromatic ring of homogentisate to yield maleylacetoacetate
SurE Nucleotidase that shows phosphatase activity on nucleoside 5'-monophosphates
Malic_M,malic Malic enzyme, NAD binding domain
Inhibitor_I42 Chagasin family peptidase inhibitor I42
Iron_traffic Could be a mediator in iron transactions between iron acquisition and iron-requiring processes, such as synthesis and or repair of Fe-S clusters in biosynthetic enzymes
T2SSC Type II secretion system protein C

M20_dimer,Peptidase_M20 Catalyzes the hydrolysis of N-succinyl-L,L- diaminopimelic acid (SDAP), forming succinate and LL-2,6- diaminoheptanedioate (DAP), an intermediate involved in the bacterial biosynthesis of lysine and meso-diaminopimelic acid, an essential component of bacterial cell walls
SDF Belongs to the dicarboxylate amino acid cation symporter (DAACS) (TC 2.A.23) family
Glyco_hydro_3 Glycosyl hydrolase family 3 N terminal domain

ATP_bind_3 Catalyzes the ATP-dependent 2-thiolation of cytidine in position 32 of tRNA, to form 2-thiocytidine (s(2)C32). The sulfur atoms are provided by the cysteine cysteine desulfurase (IscS) system
- 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose transferase and related glycosyltransferases of PMT family
EPSP_synthase Cell wall formation. Adds enolpyruvyl to UDP-N- acetylglucosamine

Hydrolase_3 Involved in the biosynthesis of lipopolysaccharides (LPSs). Catalyzes the hydrolysis of 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonate 8-phosphate (KDO 8-P) to 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonate (KDO) and inorganic phosphate

LptC Involved in the assembly of lipopolysaccharide (LPS). Required for the translocation of LPS from the inner membrane to the outer membrane. Facilitates the transfer of LPS from the inner membrane to the periplasmic protein LptA. Could be a docking site for LptA
ABC_tran,BCA_ABC_TP_C Branched-chain amino acid ATP-binding cassette transporter
Glycos_trans_3N,Glycos_transf_3 Catalyzes the transfer of the phosphoribosyl group of 5- phosphorylribose-1-pyrophosphate (PRPP) to anthranilate to yield N-(5'-phosphoribosyl)-anthranilate (PRA)
PemK_toxin PemK-like, MazF-like toxin of type II toxin-antitoxin system
tRNA-synt_2,tRNA_anti-codon tRNA synthetases class II (D, K and N)
ABC_tran Part of the ABC transporter complex LolCDE involved in the translocation of lipoproteins, in an ATP-dependent manner
MutH Sequence-specific endonuclease that cleaves unmethylated GATC sequences. It is involved in DNA mismatch repair

GAD,tRNA-synt_2,tRNA_anti-codon Aspartyl-tRNA synthetase with relaxed tRNA specificity since it is able to aspartylate not only its cognate tRNA(Asp) but also tRNA(Asn). Reaction proceeds in two steps L-aspartate is first activated by ATP to form Asp-AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Asp Asn)
AAA_26 Catalyzes a mechanistically unusual reaction, the ATP- dependent insertion of CO2 between the N7 and N8 nitrogen atoms of 7,8-diaminopelargonic acid (DAPA) to form an ureido ring

Abhydrolase_1,Abhydrolase_6 The physiological role of BioH is to remove the methyl group introduced by BioC when the pimeloyl moiety is complete. It allows to synthesize pimeloyl-ACP via the fatty acid synthetic pathway through the hydrolysis of the ester bonds of pimeloyl-ACP esters
Aminotran_1_2 Aminotransferase class I and II
BATS,Radical_SAM Catalyzes the conversion of dethiobiotin (DTB) to biotin by the insertion of a sulfur atom into dethiobiotin via a radical- based mechanism
CoaE Catalyzes the phosphorylation of the 3'-hydroxyl group of dephosphocoenzyme A to form coenzyme A
ZapD Cell division factor that enhances FtsZ-ring assembly. Directly interacts with FtsZ and promotes bundling of FtsZ protofilaments, with a reduction in FtsZ GTPase activity

SEC-C,SecA_DEAD,SecA_PP_bind,SecA_SW Part of the Sec protein translocase complex. Interacts with the SecYEG preprotein conducting channel. Has a central role in coupling the hydrolysis of ATP to the transfer of proteins into and across the cell membrane, serving both as a receptor for the preprotein-SecB complex and as an ATP-driven molecular motor driving the stepwise translocation of polypeptide chains across the membrane
Amidohydro_1 hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in cyclic amides
adh_short Belongs to the short-chain dehydrogenases reductases (SDR) family
Arginase Catalyzes the conversion of N-formimidoyl-L-glutamate to L-glutamate and formamide
T4BSS_DotI_IcmL Type-IV b secretion system, inner-membrane complex component
Toluene_X Outer membrane protein transport protein (OMPP1/FadL/TodX)
ADH_N,ADH_zinc_N Catalyzes the NAD( )-dependent oxidation of L-threonine to 2-amino-3-ketobutyrate
Aminotran_1_2 Catalyzes the cleavage of 2-amino-3-ketobutyrate to glycine and acetyl-CoA

HGTP_anticodon,tRNA-synt_2b,tRNA_edit Catalyzes the attachment of proline to tRNA(Pro) in a two-step reaction proline is first activated by ATP to form Pro- AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Pro). As ProRS can inadvertently accommodate and process non-cognate amino acids such as alanine and cysteine, to avoid such errors it has two additional distinct editing activities against alanine. One activity is designated as 'pretransfer' editing and involves the tRNA(Pro)-independent hydrolysis of activated Ala-AMP. The other activity is designated 'posttransfer' editing and involves deacylation of mischarged Ala-tRNA(Pro). The misacylated Cys- tRNA(Pro) is not edited by ProRS
MMR_HSR1,YchF-GTPase_C ATPase that binds to both the 70S ribosome and the 50S ribosomal subunit in a nucleotide-independent manner
Pept_tRNA_hydro The natural substrate for this enzyme may be peptidyl- tRNAs which drop off the ribosome during protein synthesis
Ribosomal_L25p,Ribosomal_TL5_C This is one of the proteins that binds to the 5S RNA in the ribosome where it forms part of the central protuberance
Ribosomal_L21p This protein binds to 23S rRNA in the presence of protein L20
Ribosomal_L27 Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bL27 family

GTP1_OBG,MMR_HSR1 An essential GTPase which binds GTP, GDP and possibly (p)ppGpp with moderate affinity, with high nucleotide exchange rates and a fairly low GTP hydrolysis rate. Plays a role in control of the cell cycle, stress response, ribosome biogenesis and in those bacteria that undergo differentiation, in morphogenesis control
YdjM LexA-binding, inner membrane-associated putative hydrolase
Stealth_CR1,Stealth_CR2 Stealth protein CR1, conserved region 1
MutS_I,MutS_II,MutS_III,MutS_IV,MutS_V that it carries out the mismatch recognition step. This protein has a weak ATPase activity
TamB TamB, inner membrane protein subunit of TAM complex
ALAD Belongs to the ALAD family
ATP-cone,Ribonuc_red_lgC,Ribonuc_red_lgN Provides the precursors necessary for DNA synthesis. Catalyzes the biosynthesis of deoxyribonucleotides from the corresponding ribonucleotides
Ribonuc_red_sm Provides the precursors necessary for DNA synthesis. Catalyzes the biosynthesis of deoxyribonucleotides from the corresponding ribonucleotides
tRNA-synt_2,tRNA_anti-codon Belongs to the class-II aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
PCRF,RF-1 Peptide chain release factor 2 directs the termination of translation in response to the peptide chain termination codons UGA and UAA

Sigma70_r2,Sigma70_r3,Sigma70_r4 Sigma factors are initiation factors that promote the attachment of RNA polymerase to specific initiation sites and are then released. This sigma factor controls the expression of flagella-related genes

DHHA1,tRNA-synt_2c,tRNA_SAD Catalyzes the attachment of alanine to tRNA(Ala) in a two-step reaction alanine is first activated by ATP to form Ala- AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Ala). Also edits incorrectly charged Ser-tRNA(Ala) and Gly-tRNA(Ala) via its editing domain

RecA Can catalyze the hydrolysis of ATP in the presence of single-stranded DNA, the ATP-dependent uptake of single-stranded DNA by duplex DNA, and the ATP-dependent hybridization of homologous single-stranded DNAs. It interacts with LexA causing its activation and leading to its autocatalytic cleavage
LpxK Transfers the gamma-phosphate of ATP to the 4'-position of a tetraacyldisaccharide 1-phosphate intermediate (termed DS-1- P) to form tetraacyldisaccharide 1,4'-bis-phosphate (lipid IVA)

ABC_membrane,ABC_tran Involved in lipid A export and possibly also in glycerophospholipid export and for biogenesis of the outer membrane. Transmembrane domains (TMD) form a pore in the inner membrane and the ATP-binding domain (NBD) is responsible for energy generation
Topoisom_I Eukaryotic DNA topoisomerase I, catalytic core
